h dynamic class loading, but it seems manageable with static test classes. Overall, nothing too alarming stands out!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Examining potential build issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm running through possible concerns about modifying the build file when the instructions specify to only change the test files and necessary reachability metadata. We've made adjustments already. I wonder if `spring-boot-dependencies:4.0.2` has a Maven BOM, and it seems it does. The TCK might set `libraryVersion` correctly to 4.0.2, which is good. I also need to ensure packages like `com.example...` are accessible, even if they're not scanned. Overall, many potential issues seem manageable!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering configuration dependencies**\\\\n\\\\nI need to think about whether the `PersistenceExceptionTranslationAutoConfiguration` has the right conditions. It requires `ConfigurationClassPostProcessor` in `AnnotationConfigApplicationContext`, which, thankfully, is included by default. So that's a good sign. Keeping an eye on these dependencies is important, as it helps ensure everything runs smoothly. I’ll continue to check for other potential issues, but for now, it seems like we’re on the right track with this one!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating configuration order**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about whether the `RepositoryConfiguration` class needs to be created before the postprocessor. Since BPP registration happens before singletons, that seems good. However, I worry about a potential issue with native image dynamic proxies and the agent in `javaTest` recording JDK proxy creation. I might also need to look into a `git diff` to see if there are any relevant changes or details I should be aware of.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_KIA2rfcLX6QSEW64a2WLhsHH|fc_0f64a996f45dc5bc016a0c43fedc7c8194aadb375a325d4d7c\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\":